node.title: Photos: Deadly storms and tornadoes strike central U.S.
node.description: Severe storms, including tornadoes, swept across the central U.S. overnight. The Kentucky governor said at least 70 people died in his state.
node.content: ["People survey damage from a tornado is seen in Mayfield, Kentucky, on Saturday, December 11, 2021. Tornadoes and severe weather caused catastrophic damage across multiple states late Friday into Saturday."]
